– 2 –
23 equipment rental property of the heavy equipment rental company for the
24 immediately preceding fiscal year. Under section 15, if the amount of the recovery
25 fees collected by the heavy equipment rental company during the immediately
26 preceding fiscal year exceeds the taxes levied on the heavy equipment rental
27 property of the heavy equipment rental company for the immediately preceding
28 fiscal year, the heavy equipment rental company is required to pay the excess, on a
29 pro rata basis, to the county treasurer of each county that levied property taxes on
30 the heavy equipment rental property. Finally, section 15: (1) requires each county
31 treasurer receiving such a payment to apportion the payment to the State and local
32 governments in the same manner that property taxes are apportioned; and (2)
33 provides that the requirement for a heavy equipment rental company to pay excess
34 recovery fees to a county treasurer is enforced in the same manner as the payment
35 of property taxes.
36 Sections 4-10 of this bill define certain terms relating to the imposition of the
37 recovery fee on the rental of heavy equipment rental property. Section 3 of this bill
38 establishes the applicability of those definitions.
39 Sections 11 and 12 of this bill establish provisions governing the retention and
40 examination of records relevant to the recovery fee. Section 16 of this bill provides
41 that a person who submits a false or fraudulent report concerning the recovery fee
42 or falsifies entries in or keeps more than one set of books, records or accounts with
43 intent to evade the tax is guilty of a gross misdemeanor.
